op-level profile narrative","gap_type":"curated_but_underrepresented","why_it_matters":"These are differentiating signals for this market and convert the profile from generic software architecture into production AI platform ownership.","current_state":"The evidence exists in curated role and project files, but the current summary is dominated by AdTech modernization and does not foreground evaluation, guardrails, workflow plugins, or structured-output/tooling architecture.","safe_interpretation":"Describe the candidate as a hands-on AI platform architect with production workflow, retrieval-quality, and control-plane experience.","recommended_action":"Surface Commander-4 and Lantern evidence in the headline/summary and reorder top experience bullets so AI platform architecture appears before tool detail.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:282","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:332","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:354","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:9","data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3"],"citation":"Curated AI platform proof is strong, but it is underrepresented in the current top-level representation compared with the category’s emphasis on production AI productization."},{"signal":"Business-to-technical translation and roadmap ownership","gap_type":"curated_but_underrepresented","why_it_matters":"This is a category table-stakes signal and one of the main reasons this profile can compete despite lacking literal executive scope.","current_state":"Stakeholder translation, risk communication, and business-metric realization are present in curated role evidence but are not prominent in the current summary or role-priority snapshot.","safe_interpretation":"Frame the candidate as the technical owner who translated business constraints into architecture, priorities, and shipped execution.","recommended_action":"Pull one stakeholder-translation bullet into the summary and top-role ordering, ideally alongside platform and reliability evidence.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:123","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:250","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:266","data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3"],"citation":"The evidence is already curated, but the current representation does not surface it proportionally to category demand."},{"signal":"Greenfield plus modernization range across the work history","gap_type":"curated_but_underrepresented","why_it_matters":"The category rewards candidates who can both launch new systems and evolve existing ones; current representation over-indexes on modernization only.","current_state":"The master-CV priority view is almost entirely Seven.One-centric, while curated Samdock evidence shows 0→1 platform launch, stakeholder discovery, and team delivery.","safe_interpretation":"Use non-current roles to prove range across greenfield build, domain modeling, and scalable platform design without relabeling them as AI leadership.","recommended_action":"Surface one Samdock bullet in the master summary or high-priority experience set to complement the Seven.One modernization story.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:27","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:44","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:94","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:142"],"citation":"Curated Samdock evidence broadens category fit, but it is currently absent from the representation layer’s priority set."},{"signal":"Explicit remote-first or distributed execution proof","gap_type":"unsupported_or_unsafe","why_it_matters":"Remote/global context is structurally common in the category, but it should not be claimed without direct evidence.","current_state":"The category is remote/global, yet the provided curated and upstream summaries do not supply explicit remote-first, distributed-team, or cross-time-zone delivery evidence.","safe_interpretation":"Do not convert current international context or employer brand into a direct remote/global execution claim.","recommended_action":"Leave remote/global leadership out of the core narrative unless explicit source evidence is found and curated.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3"],"citation":"The category expects remote/distributed fluency, but the provided record does not explicitly document it."},{"signal":"Executive org ownership, P&L, and broad people-management scope","gap_type":"unsupported_or_unsafe","why_it_matters":"This category should not be approached with inflated executive claims; the market signal is player-coach, not org-builder.","current_state":"The record supports mentoring, promotions, and elements of hiring, but it does not explicitly support budget ownership, P&L, large-scale org building, or broad performance-management authority.","safe_interpretation":"Claim mentoring, hiring participation, and technical leadership; avoid Head/VP/C-suite and org-builder language.","recommended_action":"Keep leadership wording anchored to technical direction, standards, mentoring, and delivery ownership.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:182","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:217"],"citation":"Current evidence supports player-coach leadership, not executive org ownership."},{"signal":"Broad cloud-platform authority beyond directly evidenced AWS delivery","gap_type":"unsupported_or_unsafe","why_it_matters":"The category allows selective infrastructure keywords, but overclaiming Kubernetes/Terraform/GitOps/Helm can damage credibility.","current_state":"AWS-native platform delivery is evidenced, but the provided curated record does not directly support Kubernetes, GitOps, Terraform, or Helm authority.","safe_interpretation":"Use AWS, observability, monitoring, and event-driven infrastructure language where directly supported; avoid broader cloud-platform branding.","recommended_action":"Keep infrastructure wording tied to CloudFront, EventBridge, ECS, OpenSearch, CloudWatch, SNS, and the observed platform outcomes.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:71","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:163"],"citation":"The evidence is strong for AWS-native delivery and observability, but not for the broader infrastructure tool set flagged as risky in this category."}],"safe_claims_now":{"headline_safe":["Engineering Leader / Software Architect","Technical Lead | AI platform and systems architecture","AI Systems Architect focused on production delivery and reliability"],"profile_safe":["Hands-on architect/player-coach who translates business needs into technical execution for production platforms.","Built and modernized event-driven platforms with measurable reliability gains, including 75% incident reduction and 3 years zero downtime.","Led AI workflow and retrieval-quality improvements for an enterprise platform serving 2,000 users with 42 plugins.","Combines platform architecture, observability, evaluation, and implementation depth in TypeScript/Python systems."],"experience_safe":["Transformed a legacy AdTech platform into autonomous event-driven TypeScript microservices on AWS.","Architected observability and monitoring capabilities that improved issue detection, MTTR, and live-service stability.","Introduced DDD and engineering standards that reduced onboarding from 6 to 3 months, improved velocity by 25%, and reduced requirement misalignment by 40%.","Built enterprise AI platform capabilities including hybrid retrieval, semantic caching, structured outputs, and LLM-as-judge evaluation.","Architected a 0→1 event-sourced CRM platform and led stakeholder event-storming/domain-discovery work."],"leadership_safe":["Established architectural direction and secured stakeholder buy-in for technical-debt and system-health investment.","Mentored 10+ senior engineers on architectural patterns and promoted 3 engineers to lead positions.","Led elements of software-engineer hiring, including selection criteria, interview strategy, and technical assessments.","Shaped engineering practices through DDD, reviews, standards, and cross-functional delivery leadership."],"unsafe_or_too_weak":["Head of AI, VP of AI, Chief AI Officer, or equivalent executive-title claims.","Budget, P&L, or broad org-building ownership.","Formal people-management scope beyond what is explicitly documented.","Remote-global team leadership or regional expansion ownership.","Kubernetes, GitOps, Terraform, or Helm authority.","Fine-tuning pipelines, custom embedding training, RLHF, or research-led ML narrative."],"citations":["data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:88","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:123","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:182","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:217","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:282","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:27","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:44","data/master-cv/projects/commander4_skills.json:42","data/master-cv/projects/lantern_skills.json:49"]},"representation_diagnosis":{"well_represented_now":["Seven.One legacy modernization, architecture, and reliability outcomes are already prominent.","AI project depth is visible through Commander-4 and Lantern project priority slots.","Skills already show Python, retrieval evaluation, semantic caching, LLM gateway design, and related AI-platform tooling."],"underrepresented_now":["Top-level headline/summary do not clearly position the profile as an AI-platform architect/player-coach.","Business-to-technical translation and stakeholder alignment are weaker in representation than in the curated evidence.","Evaluation, guardrails, and structured-output/tool-calling signals are not surfaced strongly enough outside project detail.","Greenfield range from Samdock is missing from the priority narrative.","Mentoring and practice shaping are available but not framed as delivery leverage."],"overstated_risk_now":["The generic 'Engineering Leader' headline can be read as broader management ownership than the evidence cleanly supports.","The current summary leans so heavily on one modernization story that it obscures the stronger AI-platform fit.","The skills block is tool-dense and can read broader than the higher-value architecture and outcome story.","Representation is proxy-derived rather than a canonical finalized master-CV artifact."],"representation_priorities":["Re-anchor the headline around Technical Lead / AI Platform / Systems Architecture rather than generic leadership wording.","Blend AI platform, reliability, and business-translation proof into the summary instead of using only the AdTech modernization story.","Reorder Seven.One bullet priority so AI platform architecture and stakeholder translation appear alongside reliability proof.","Surface one curated Samdock greenfield/platform bullet to show range.","Trim skills emphasis toward evidence-dense platform and quality terms rather than a broad tool inventory."],"citations":["data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:123","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:282","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:7","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:7","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:27"]},"curation_priorities":[{"priority_rank":1,"action":"Promote Seven.One safe title provenance from upstream STAR records into curated role metadata.","why_now":"This immediately improves category-safe framing and reduces dependence on the generic current headline while staying below executive inflation